	    return -1;", "explanation": "This sanity check executes AFTER compressed_data was allocated at line 47 and read at line 54, and it returns -1 without free(compressed_data). A crafted image with an out-of-range image_pagesize therefore leaks page_len bytes on every call; because pagenum/pages can be iterated by the attacker this is an unbounded memory leak (resource exhaustion / DoS). The fix is to free(compressed_data) on this early-return path (or move the pagesize validation before the allocation)."}, {"file": "corpus/train/train_0182_cwe295.cpp", "lines": "22-24", "code": "for(size_t i = 0;i <= af->image_pagesize - af->image_sectorsize;
