				}", "explanation": "The RESUME branch handles a partially-transferred file being resumed. For RESUME the port to match is taken from Token(3) (not Token(4) as elsewhere) into uResumePort. It then walks the module's entire socket set via BeginSockets()/EndSockets(), C-style casts each CSocket* to CDCCBounce* (line 31), and compares that bounce's local (ZNC-side) port to the requested resume port. On a match it forwards a rewritten DCC RESUME line to the user, substituting the matched bounce's real user-side port (pSock->GetUserPort()) so the resume offset lines up with the correct relayed connection. sFile and Token(4) are echoed through unchanged."}, {"file": "corpus/train/train_0246_cwe399.cpp", "lines": "37-46", "code": "			} else if (sType.Equals("ACCEPT")) {
				// Need to lookup the connection by port, filter the port, and forward to the user
